If a tech startup wants to break into the Islamic and Chinese markets, it has to first learn what those customers want and then adapt its goods and services accordingly. Cultural appropriateness and language localization are two factors to think about. All materials and communications must be translated and presented in a manner that is readily accessible for Chinese customers while also respecting the cultural and religious values of the Muslim market. Reaching and engaging these demographics may also be aided by forging relationships and collaborations with local companies and influencers. 